[449.309027, "i", "cat > /app/NUMPY2_COMPATIBILITY_CHANGES.md << 'EOF'\n# Numpy 2.0 Compatibility Changes for pyknotid 0.5.3\n\n## Summary\nSuccessfully compiled and installed pyknotid from source with Numpy 2.3.0 compatibility.\nAll Cython extensions (chelpers, ccomplexity, cinvariants) are working correctly.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. Python 3.13 Compatibility\n**File: pyknotid/make/torus.py**\n- Changed: `from fractions import gcd` → `from math import gcd`\n- Reason: In Python 3.9+, gcd was moved from fractions to math module\n\n### 2. Numpy 2.0 Type Compatibility\nReplaced deprecated numpy type aliases with their explicit equivalents:\n\n**Files affected:**\n- pyknotid/spacecurves/spacecurve.py\n- pyknotid/make/periodic_knot.py\n- pyknotid/spacecurves/knot.py\n- pyknotid/spacecurves/openknot.py\n- pyknotid/representations/dtnotation.py\n- pyknotid/representations/representation.py\n\n**Changes:**\n- `n.float` → `n.float64`\n- `n.int` → `n.int64`\n- `n.complex` → `n.complex128` (for dtype)\n- `isinstance(x, n.complex)` → `isinstance(x, (comp"]
[449.309328, "i", "lex, n.complexfloating))`\n\n**File: pyknotid/invariants.py**\n- Line 137: Updated dtype assignment to use n.complex128 and proper isinstance check\n- Line 177: Updated isinstance check for complex types\n\n## Installation Steps Performed\n1. Cloned pyknotid v0.5.3 from GitHub\n2. Installed build dependencies (setuptools, cython)\n3. Applied Numpy 2.0 compatibility fixes\n4. Built Cython extensions using `python3 setup.py build_ext --inplace`\n5. Installed to global Python environment using `python3 setup.py install`\n\n## Verification\n- All Cython extensions compiled successfully\n- Test suite passed (18/18 tests in test_knot.py and test_spacecurve.py)\n- README example code runs without errors\n- Extensions loaded from: /usr/local/lib/python3.13/site-packages/pyknotid/\n\n## Environment\n- Python: 3.13.7\n- Numpy: 2.3.0\n- Cython: 3.2.4\nEOF\n"]
[449.309517, "o", "cat > /app/NUMPY2_COMPATIBILITY_CHANGES.md << 'EOF'\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r"]
